rComments: he seemed really nice at the beginning but as the semester went on he something changed. The class content was fair, he gave other chances if you missed presentations my only issue is his communication, I emailed him about something very important and still waiting for a response, I almost think he won't ever respond and I would like one.

He was a great teacher, he really cared even though our cameras weren't on he was very understanding, his fiche de lectures are very fair and its very easy to do well since you just need to do the work and you can do amazing!! Hes the best!!!

This was an 8:30am class and did most of it in bed. Pretty boring, same format every week, and didn't help at all with the HSS class. Easy GPA boost, assignments are straight forward and identical to what you do in class. I thought he was nice, at least online. You gotta participate a bit otherwise it's so awkward and dead silent during class.
He is not bad at all, a fair grader, and tests you on what you learned.
very good. do homework and exercise, the high mark will be yours.

Unfortunately, he didn't really make the content from the main class easier to understand. His class was pretty dry, but the assignments and exams were extremely easy. He's okay in general; not nearly as bad as other people are saying. Very fair grader, so if you think you deserve marks where you didn't get them, you should talk to him.

I was scared to have him after reading these reviews but he honestly wasn't that bad. The class was well structured and made sense. It was also an incredibly easy course and a great gpa booster. He does hit the table sometimes though so try not to get him mad lol

He's nice but often tends to teach as if no one else is in the room except for when doing an activity. We got about a month and a half behind in content because we spent a month reviewing a topic no one needed extra time on. That said, his assignments and exams are clear and easy to pass.

To be honest, his class wasn't extremely tough; make sure you show up to class and do well on your assignments (as well as hand them in, in person) and you should be more than fine. This class is a really good GPA booster and the midterm/exam is in the same format as the assignments. The prof himself is inconsistent and sometimes hard to understand

This prof is very weird. At first, he seemed to be a smart french teacher, but then I realized this man has no common sense or memory. Calls people by their last names and can't remember anything. The course is easy although you're marked on very few things. So do well on his assignments and you should be ok. Midterms & final exam are quite easy.

This professor is very problematic . I did not improve my French speaking skills AT ALL even though this is an oral course. Record ALL of your conversations with him as well as have written proof of what you discussed because he forgets and blames you . Grades unfairly and thinks his opinion is the only one that counts. AVOID AT ALL COSTS!

He is the worst professor Ive had in my 4 years at the university of Ottawa. Thisclass was a waste of time and I HONESTLY didnt learn ANYTHING. We spent each and every class reading directly from the text book. His grading is also an unfair and inconsistent. He also went the whole semester without learning any of our names. AVOID THIS CLASS

I'm a straight A student. I have asked for clarification and help to improve my marks throughout the semester, instead subjected to a humiliating French grammar class for beginners. The whole point of FLS is it's French as a second language. The class was informed that its normal to make mistakes. I'm telling you it's not, hence why the "D".

Well, your French will improve because there are weekly assignments based on the readings for the core class. Participate whenever you can, because he gets angry if you don't (and tends to slap the table, which is not fun).
I did not enjoy his class. As a person, i am sure he is fine, but he should not be a teacher. He is teasing to hear himself speak. GOD AWFUL

Take another prof for this class. He is very rude and interrupts people just to share his point of view. If you have to take him, record important conversations that you have with him because he will forget and tell that you are wrong. He is ALWAYS right and when ppl dont understand, he never thinks that its bc he didnt explain enough.

Two things made our conversation class painful: M. Dossous interrupts people frequently, and is not very good at seeing raised hands. This discouraged participation when that was the goal of the course. Otherwise interesting to listen to (he did lots of the talking).

dont even bother sending him any emails because he wont read them. in fact, dont bother going to class either because hes not helpful if you have questions. in fact, just dont even take a course with him.

He is the worst prof I have ever had in university.  He basically picks a bunch of topics to discuss instead of actually teaching us how to communicate in French and then rants about them for an hour and a half.  He also makes his midterms seem really easy and then gives bad marks without any feedback.  He makes it impossible to improve.  Just dont

Picks highly controversial topics and rants about his opinions on them the entire class. Does not give clear expectations about assignments. I signed up for a French speaking class but barely spoke French the entire semester. I really tried to give him  a chance, but being in this class was an incredibly frustrating experience!

Explains the material thoroughly and does not mind repeating. Encourages students to ask questions and is always ready to help during his office hours. If you pay attention in class, do the homework and ask questions, you will be more than fine! :)

He wasn't terrible but wasn't great either. He's super passionate about the language which is a rare treat however he will encourage you to participate then be rude and judgemental when you do. Assignments are easy, tests much tougher. Homework was unrelated to class content and he often didn't fully explain concepts that were emphasized on tests

He is passive aggressive towards students, hard to follow, gives no feedback, doesn't hand out the mandatory attendance until the end of class, is rude, cuts people off, boring and repetitive lectures about simple concepts of grammar.

Did next to no work (no studying required) and got a good mark- he marks easy on presentations and harder on exams just make sure you follow what he wants. He is easy to understand. Lectures are super boring, he chooses awful subjects but all you really need to do is take notes (for reference at the exams) and give your input when he calls on you.
RUN FOREST RUN!
Worst professor in the whole department. Apparently he's had numerous complaints against him so I'm not sure why the faculty still employs him. Avoid at all costs.

Small class. Doesn't care to know your name. Terrible exams. No feedback. No help.  Lectures make you feel stressed, speaks way too fast.  Would've rather taken a French course on a weekend then have taken this class with this professor. No thanks, never again.

This guy made me want to stop studying French. He talks full speed ahead, without breaking concepts down to an understandable level. His exams were easy but hardly addressed anything we learned. He reads from the textbook, that's about it. Don't take this class if you want to learn anything.

Quite possibly one of the worst teachers I've ever had. Doesn't care about students and won't even try to learn your name. He provides no relevant feedback which makes it impossible to improve your skills and get better marks. He picks terrible topics to talk about for a French oral class. Try to avoid his classes if you want to improve in French!

He takes up the questions he assigns for homework and is willing to answer or cover anything that you have problems with in class. Homework is optional and there is just tests and the exam which he always gives detailed revisions for. He speaks fast and his writing is hard to read sometimes but its easy to pass with good marks. I'd take him again.

This professor does not use rubrics and therefore, improvement is very difficult. After much insistence, I was able to meet with him and finally get a sense of how to do better. The topics are interesting however the way of marking is ALWAYS the same so be careful.
Speaks very quickly, writes illegibly on the board, doesn't answer questions because he can only explain things one way. Boring class, not a good prof, but easy exams.

He has a habit of teaching very forcefully and so always sounding somewhat angry, but he's also patient, methodical, and genuinely accomodating. He's certainly easier to pay attention to than most professors teaching grammar courses.

This class was the most painful I've ever had to deal with. He's completely arrogant and condescending if you ask a question or have a rebuttal, and the coursework is completely boring. Quizzes were generally easy, but overall I would not EVER take a class with him again.
WORST FRENCH PROF EVER!! should not be teaching beginner french at all becuase of his lack of english. If you are just learning french, AVOID TAKING IT WITH HIM!!

Quite a depressing experience, this class. I was looking forward to it too. Thought I'd get to practise my writing skills. Problem is: there are no assignments in this class. Only tests and optional homework. Once I was the only person in class who did the homework, and so I was asked to share it with the class. Then the prof insinuates that I
very difficult to understand...says one thing and does another - goes off on random tangents regarding things that have nothing to do with class

He was a pushover and allowed several immature students more or less run the class. The day of a test, if they felt they werent ready or in the mood, they would make him reschedule it. they pushed and bullied him all semester and he made it easy for them. By the end he made a sad attempt to get things back under control...too late. C's for everyon
HES CLASS IS SO BORiNG! He attempts to be funny ....try again prof! If you think French is boring don't take this class  you'll  wan't to muder the language!

Mr. Dossous gave me an F as my final grade, so I emailed him to ask for justification as I had attended all classes and done all assignments. After waiting a month for a reply, he insisted that I was not there for the final exam. I had to take the matter to the department, where they found I should have received an A-. Way to go Dossous.
